  "texts": [
    "If the HDS scheme is used together with the STS one, their global time step is set to be equal, t STS = t HDS.",
    "The computational domain is discretized with a three-dimensional Cartesian grid that is constant in time.",
    "By default, the code uses a uniform grid that can have different grid spacing in different directions.",
    "It perfectly fits performing realistic simulations of the solar and stellar atmospheres, as modeling of turbulent convective flows requires a fine uniform grid in all directions.",
    "However, other tasks, like wave propagation can have very elongated computational domain in one direction."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}